The key is to observe that the вҖңmessyвҖҷвҖҷ radical really does simplify.  First compute

  yвҖІ(x)=d/dx\Bigl(\tfrac{x^4}{4}+\tfrac1{8x^2}\Bigr)
        =x^3\;-\;\frac1{4x^3}
        =\frac{4x^6-1}{4x^3}\,.

Hence

  1+(yвҖІ)^2
  =1+\frac{(4x^6-1)^2}{16x^6}
  =\frac{16x^6+(4x^6-1)^2}{16x^6}
  =\frac{(4x^6+1)^2}{16x^6}\,.

Thus for x>0,

  вҲҡ[\,1+(yвҖІ)^2\,]
  =\frac{4x^6+1}{4x^3}
  =x^3+\frac1{4x^3}\,.

So the arcвҖҗlength is

  L=вҲ«вӮҒВІвҲҡ[1+(yвҖІ)^2]dx
   =вҲ«вӮҒВІ\Bigl(x^3+\frac1{4x^3}\Bigr)dx
   =\Bigl[\frac{x^4}{4}-\frac1{8x^2}\Bigr]_{1}^{2}
   =\Bigl(\frac{16}{4}-\frac1{32}\Bigr)-\Bigl(\frac14-\frac18\Bigr)
   =\frac{123}{32}
   вүҲ3.84375\,.
